Pappaladro's sisters spoke of her passion for nature and reading and dreams of writing children's books.

‘She believed in God, the saints, the power of prayer and love and even in magic,’ her sister, Mona Harris, said.

Judge Tina Nadeau questioned whether the outcome would have been the same had Smeltzer not used drugs that night.

