But she acknowledged that he must have had an extreme emotional reaction to what greeted him when he came home.

She said nothing she could do or say would lessen the grief for the families and imposed the sentence the state requested.

It included a provision that five years will be suspended if he earns his college degree and takes anger management classes.

With the suspension and credit for time served since his arrest, he could be free in nine years. Mercey now lives with one of her mother's sisters.

